    <title>Bounds on the dimension of trivariate spline spaces: A homological
  approach</title>
    <summary>  We consider the vector space of globally differentiable piecewise polynomial
functions defined on a three-dimensional polyhedral domain partitioned into
tetrahedra. We prove new lower and upper bounds on the dimension of this space
by applying homological techniques. We give an insight into different ways of
approaching this problem by exploring its connections with the Hilbert series
of ideals generated by powers of linear forms, fat points, the so-called
Fr\"oberg-Iarrobino conjecture, and the weak Lefschetz property.
</summary>
